102
00:10:01,779 --> 00:10:04,900
Well, what do you do in the city when you don't like the process of the charter?

103
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,941
Anybody can do a charter, change the charter.

104
00:10:08,001 --> 00:10:09,781
It's not something exclusive to us.

105
00:10:10,722 --> 00:10:26,166
And I think one of the things that we need to do is, first of all, have a process in place for our committee so that those folks who were there the other night have an opportunity to identify in this lengthy,

106
00:10:27,175 --> 00:10:28,922
If you've read the Charter, you know how lengthy it is.

107
00:10:28,982 --> 00:10:31,694
If you've read the general laws, you know how even more lengthy it is.

108
00:10:32,613 --> 00:10:49,386
but if you have an issue in the city on how the city does one thing, it may not be the, you know, how many years the mayor is in or the real highlight issues, but there are small issues that I may want to, you know, submit for an amendment to change the way we do things.

109
00:10:49,947 --> 00:10:54,770
And I think that we owe it to the folks who are building this charter.

110
00:10:54,790 --> 00:11:00,335
And it's, I know where nine of us are kind of the vessel for everybody to get this done, but,

111
00:11:01,487 --> 00:11:08,737
