112
00:11:09,561 --> 00:11:20,308
soon give them an opportunity to communicate with us better and tell us, hey, I don't like, and I always use this example, I don't like how the trees are planted on this street.

113
00:11:20,828 --> 00:11:31,334
Well, whatever that process is, how do I come to us and say, I want an amendment in the charter now that we're going through this that says, instead of this, I want it done this way.

114
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:33,075
And that's a small example.

115
00:11:33,195 --> 00:11:38,819
There are other major examples that, you know, my personal feeling is the school committee's

116
00:11:40,245 --> 00:11:44,808
policies and procedures are not, you know, need to be reviewed.

117
00:11:45,308 --> 00:11:53,514
And I think they need to be reviewed because they're not in the charter, they're just general laws and we can update them and we can change those.

118
00:11:53,574 --> 00:11:59,238
But my goal is to make sure that this is a living document, that not it's 40 years from now will be looked at again.

119
00:11:59,838 --> 00:12:02,840
It should be a process that says, I want this.

120
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,302
And I also think, you know, we heard clearly

121
00:12:05,922 --> 00:12:09,945
from those folks, you know, public participation is key.

122
00:12:10,465 --> 00:12:13,388
And I think that this is where we started.

123
00:12:13,768 --> 00:12:18,071
You have the right to participate in how your city is governed.

124
00:12:18,491 --> 00:12:21,133
And if everybody agrees with you, then it should be changed.

125
00:12:21,173 --> 00:12:27,758
So those are the things that I, you know, I thought that the folks who presented and commented were well thought out.

126
00:12:28,779 --> 00:12:33,903
A lot of veteran citizens who've seen a lot, and some of the stuff is within our realm.

127
